Tier 1 — The Libraries EVERY Python Developer Should Learn First

These are the core building-block libraries you'll use everywhere.

1. os

For working with files, folders, system paths.

Create/delete files

Navigate directories

Get system info


Why: Needed for automation, scripting, and real projects.


---

2. sys

For interacting with Python itself.

Arguments

Exiting program

Python runtime info


Why: Useful for more “technical” scripts.


---

3. json

For saving & loading structured data.

Config files

Game saves

Bot settings

API responses


Why: Nearly every modern program uses JSON.


---

4. time

For delays, timestamps, timers.

time.sleep()

Profiling performance


Why: Used constantly in automation or bots.


---

5. random

For random numbers, choices, generators.

Games

Simulations

Small tools


Why: You’ll use it more than you expect.


---

6. typing

For writing clean code at scale.

Type hints

Optional

Dict[str, int]


Why: Helps you write professional code.
